parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of motorized seat belts can lead to occupants being unrestrained in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt locks down or fails to retract
the seat belt only moves a couple of inches
the seat belt fails to secure the latch
the seat belt track does not slide properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, leading to safety concerns and inconvenience.
symptoms: the battery needs to be replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Wiring Issues Under the Hood
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty electrical wiring under the hood can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to safety risks and potential engine damage.
symptoms: but potential symptoms may include: intermittent electrical system failures

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatback frame can cause the seat to collapse or recline unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The seatback frame bends or collapses
the driver or passenger loses support or control.
